Description: starts with an arm ball, which leaves the batsman after pitching, but Rohit late-cuts it between point and cover-point
fuller this time, and Sharma is forced to defend
again that slight swing away from the right-hand batsman. On a length. Worked to leg for one
again that slight swing , back into the left-hand bat. Defended to leg
fuller, middle and leg, defended to midwicket
quick, into the pads, nudged fine of short fine

Summary: Cummins to Rohit Sharma,4 leg byes
Description: short of a length, tight line, but it nips back in going too far down leg for four leg-byes
fuller, just outside off, holding its line. Defended
nicely played. On a length, just around middle, but Rohit does really well to get inside the line and glances him fine of short fine leg
short of a length, just outside off, defended

Summary: Cummins to Rohit Sharma,1 leg bye
Description: straying into the pads again, lucky to get away with just the one leg-bye
short of a length, 136ks, around off, pushed to point
lovely outswinger first up. Dipping, on a length, just outside off, moving away late. Just doesn't get the edge
they are feeding his pull again? After bowling a lovely outswinger, Krishna goes short, and he is not quick enough to bother Sharma, who goes over square leg. Yorks the boundary
in the air, catchable high, but pierces the gap between point and cover-point. Wide length ball, swinging away, but he throws his bat at it
short of a length, around off, worked to leg for one
he is not getting it right. Short, angling away to give him the width, and he is cut in front of backward point for four
looks for the ramp, but Krishna goes wide at it and concedes just the single to square leg
cracked away. Just short of a length, but de Kock shows no respect. Clears the front leg, hits on the up, and clears wide mid-on easily
even better. Totally disdainful. Length ball, outside off, but de Kock shows no regard. He slogs this over midwicket for four more
full, just outside off, dug out to mid-off for one
on a length, on off, Rohit is squared up a touch and ends up defending this back to Cummins
short of a length, hits the bat high as Sharma defends
looks to drive on the up but this gets a little big and hits the splice of his bat. Fielded at cover-point
full toss, crunched past the bowler for four more. Long-on has no chance of cutting this
on a length, the swing back in cramps him up on the cut

always a difficult catch. De Kock gets a massive top edge on the sweep, Varun runs back from short fine, but he has to catch it over his head running back, and they are always tricky. He gets there but can't hold on
beaten on the sweep this time, but this is headed down leg
low full toss, just the single to deep midwicket
on a length, on off, defended back to him
short of a length, straight, bunted to leg for one
short of a length, outside off, opens the face, but can't get it past cover-point
on a length, just outside off, punched down to mid-off
on a length, wicket to wicket, pushed wide of mid-on for one
de Kock looks to pull, Russell has bowled short at 137ks, gets it high, and de Kock gets just the single to deep square
yorker, middle and leg, dot
de Kock dictating terms here. Not a bad ball, short of a length, straight, but he picks the length early, swivels back and slogs this almost through square leg and along the ground
slightly fuller, de Kock respects it and opens the face for a single
fullish, straight, clipped to short midwicket
uppish drive but bounces well short of mid-off
de Kock is toying with them. Short of a length, straight, and he rocks back to pull him for a flat six over midwicket. Picking on the short boundary
beautiful batting. Gets width outside off this time so he drives hard on it, and it bounces over the straight extra cover for four. Mid-off has no chance
flighted outside off, driven hard, but straight to point
legcutter, short of a length, punched wide of long-off for an easy couple
on a length, around off, pushed down the ground to long-on
offbreak, just outside off, pushed to the right of cover for one
slower through the air, full, just outside off, defended with an open face
legcutter, Sharma looks to play on the up, but can't beat the man at cover
yorker outside off, de Kock can't reach it
nearly a yorker, well outside off, de Kock catches up with it, but only manages to send it back to Russell
de Kock on fire. Two yorkers later, Russell gives him a length ball - actually slightly fuller than length - and he clears the front leg to smack him back over his head
bouncer, and it disappears over the short boundary. Pulls this emphatically, and there is no deep square in place anyway. That is fifty for him. He looks in ominous form
back to yorkers, and draws another dot. Actually make it a single to cover
short of a length, outside off, steered to third man for one
lovely legcutter outside off, beats him on the drive
tries the slog sweep but is done in by the wrong'un this time. Lucky to survive this one
after two good balls, he serves Sharma a short ball, and he pulls him clean over midwicket. It is the short boundary too
quick legcutter, Sharma looks to drive on the up, but is beaten
on a length, slow, wicket to wicket, bunted into the leg side for one
tossed up, just outside off, defended

Summary: Shivam Mavi to Rohit Sharma,no run
Description: wide length ball, hits him high on the bat. Hit straight to point

Summary: Shivam Mavi to Rohit Sharma,FOUR runs
Description: calculated hitting. Skips down the wicket, takes this on a length, and goes inside-out to the shorter boundary. One-bounce four to deep cover
finally a wicket for KKR. Mavi comes back after that disdainful four. This is full, just outside off, Sharma plays for the angle, but it actually pitches and seams away to take the outside edge
shuffles across to play this length ball to midwicket
on a length, angling in, hits him high on the bat. Pushed to mid-on
another length ball pushed straight to mid-on
on a length, middle and off, worked to deep midwicket
legcutter, outside off, on a length, pushed towards long-on for one
short of a length, around off, punched to deep midwicket for two
short of a length, another single to deep midwicket
deftly played wide of that slip. A quick length-ball legcutter, and he opens the face late. Russell has to give chase, and he sticks the boot out
short of a length, sits up, punched wide of long-on for two

Summary: Shivam Mavi to de Kock,1 run
Description: nearly a yorker, at his heel, clipped away for one
short of a length, outside off, holds its line, beats the edge as he looks to run this down
looks to work this length ball to leg, but gets a leading edge over cover for one

Summary: Shivam Mavi to de Kock,no run
Description: shows him the ramp early, Mavi bowls the short ball, slower I think, at 126ks. De Kock continues with the ramp, but is beaten

Summary: Shivam Mavi to de Kock,1 run
Description: slower ball, wide length ball, crunched to deep cover for one

Yadav plonks his back foot across to set up a base to go over the bowler's head, but ends up going over the keeper's head with an outside edge. Just short of that driving length, but the bowler is unlucky here
wrong'un, from just outside leg, and takes the leading edge to point. Bounces short
another wrong'un, starts too far outside leg, and de Kock works it away for a single
he has swept this onto his own wicket. Varun bowls a full and wide carrom ball, Yadav tries the big sweep, and gets a meaty bottom edge onto the off stump
quick length ball outside off, left alone
on a length, outside off, knocked into the off side for one
short of a length, on off, punched to deep midwicket for one

Summary: Shivam Mavi to de Kock,2 runs
Description: full and straight, mis-hit towards deep midwicket for an easy two

Summary: Shivam Mavi to de Kock,no run
Description: slower-ball yorker, dipping on him, 102ks. Knuckle ball it looks like. Kept out by de Kock, who acknowledges it is a good ball

Summary: Shivam Mavi to de Kock,FOUR runs
Description: imperious. Short of a length, on-pace, angles outside off, and he steers it between point and short third man for four

Summary: Shivam Mavi to de Kock,SIX runs
Description: de Kock is looking for an early night here. Short ball, only about rib-high, and he swivels with it to pull it up and over and just behind square

Summary: Shivam Mavi to de Kock,1 run
Description: slower short ball, pulled down to deep midwicket for one
shuffles across, Mavi doesn't give him the length to hit. Defended off the back foot
slower ball, full toss outside leg, glanced away for one to fine leg
and Pandya stamps his hitting class. Cummins bowls just short of a length with mid-on up, and he drives at it with his head down. Doesn't bother to look up either as he has cleared mid-on with ease
bouncer, at him. Pandya ducks it
lovely straight hitting. Cummins goes full, 140ks, and he gets under it and lofts him back over his head
this is buffet bowling for Pandya. On a length, into the pads, the short boundary on the leg side. He flicks it with his head down, and clears the square-leg fence easily
bouncer to end the over, and Pandya ducks it
short and wide, just too slow, so he doesn't get the timing. Takes a the single on the cut
Pandya is looking for the golf swing as Green pitches this up. Gets a thick inside edge for one
low full toss, driven down to long-on
he over-compensates, goes too short, and gives him width too. Cut over point for four. Deliberately up and over
nearly a yorker, calmly pushed to long-off to end this early
